	<font size="-1"><b>CES Offers Discounted Travel Options For Attendees</b></font>

	<p>Arlington, VA - Jul, 21 1999
	<BR>
	To catch the first technology event of the new millennium, attendees to the 2000 International CES Your Source for Workstyle and Lifestyle Technology, to be held January 6-9, 2000 in Las Vegas Nev., should book their travel early. As the launch pad for 21st century technology, the 2000 show promises to be the best CES yet with more than 1,500 exhibitors and 90,000 attendees expected from around the globe and with leading visionaries like Eric Benhamou of 3Com, Scott McNealy of Sun Microsystems and Bill Gates of Microsoft as keynoters for its jam-packed conference program.  CES has secured discounted travel options for attendees. <P>
As in years past, we ve tried to make it as easy and affordable as possible for the consumer technology industry to attend CES,  said Robbi Lycett, CES vice president.   Because of worldwide millennium celebrations, we have noticed increased airfare rates for December and January travelers.  While we have arranged discounted airfares and other travel options, we re still urging attendees to book their flights now. <P>
CES discounted rates are available on six air carriers, 28 Las Vegas hotels and one car rental agency. Plus online registration for the show is free until December 17, 1999.  Online details on CES travel options are listed at <a href="http://www.CESweb.org/home/gen/travel.cfm">www.cesweb.org</a>.   As of July 19, CES had located round-trip airfares from the following cities:  <UL> <LI>Atlanta to Las Vegas: $397.00 <LI>Chicago to Las Vegas: $298.00 <LI>Dallas to Las Vegas: $288.88 <LI>Los Angeles to Las Vegas: $78.00 <LI>New York to Las Vegas: $318.00 <LI>Philadelphia to Las Vegas: $434.00 <LI>San Francisco to Las Vegas: $132.00 </UL> 	 <P>
	CEMA is a sector of the Electronic Industries Alliance (EIA), the 75-year-old Arlington, Virginia-based trade organization representing all facets of electronics manufacturing.  CEMA represents more than 500 U.S. manufacturers of audio, video, accessories, mobile electronics, communication, information technology and multimedia products that are sold through consumer channels.   	 <P>
As the sponsor, manager and producer of the International CES Your Source for Workstyle and Lifestyle Technology,SM CEMA reinvests all profits from CES into industry services, including technical training and education, product promotion, engineering standards development, market research, and governmental and legal affairs support.   <P>
	<BR>&nbsp;<BR>&nbsp;
	

		
